         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">29/1/84. ¶ When expressing to you, dear Sir Richard, ¶ Letter not found. ¶  ¶ my felicitation for a new year of happiness and health and all other wordly ¶ worldly? ¶  ¶ enjoyment to you, I was ill on...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.01.29a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Richard Owen</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Natural History<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Museum,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>London,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>General Library MSS, Owen correspondence, vol. XIX, f. 388.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated, apparently by Owen</seg>: Autograph of the Botanist (of Australia)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Baron</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ferd. von<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Mueller</hi>
                     </seg>.</p>
               </note>29/1/84.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">When expressing to you, dear Sir Richard,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>my felicitation for a new year of happiness and health and all other wordly<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>worldly?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>enjoyment to you, I was ill on the seaside, and then not aware, that our gracious Sovereign had conferred on you the mark of royal favor, with which you commence the new-year.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Knight Commander of the Bath, KCB, gazetted 5 January 1884<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(O<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">DNB</seg>).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Let me then, as one of the foremost of your admirers, tender now my gratulation at so happy an event, trusting that you may be long spared in unimpaired health and mental freshness to enjoy this additional wreath of laurels, which you have won so deservedly.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Indeed to me it has been for years a cause of sorrow, that your pre-eminent position in science had not received a higher acknowledgement, and occasions arose, when I gave frankly expressions to that effect in letters and otherwise.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>May then, honored Sir, this recognition, which thousands of men of science all over the globe cheeringly appreciate, add to the gladness of that life, which we all hope will be prolonged in serenity and in triumphant cognizance of great results achieved through very many years yet.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever, dear Sir Richard,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>very regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
